    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely dice the <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong> and <strong>carrot[s] </strong>(skins on)</p><p>Peel and chop the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based<strong> hob-safe oven-proof casserole dish</strong> with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced onion</strong>, <strong>diced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>garlic</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>bay leaf[ves],</strong> <strong>tomato paste </strong>and<strong> chopped tomatoes</strong></p><p>Add<strong> </strong>your<strong> red wine paste</strong> and <strong>beef stock mix </strong>with 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[260ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[340ml]</span><strong> boiled water</strong></p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>sugar</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Top with your <strong>duck leg[s]</strong></p><p>Once boiling, put the dish in the oven and cook, uncovered, for 28-30 min \u2013 this is your <strong>braised duck leg</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>halved waxy potatoes</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 20 min</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While everything's in the oven, grate your<strong> Italian hard cheese</strong></p><p>After the initial 20 min, top the potatoes with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and<strong> remaining chopped garlic</strong> and return them to the oven for a final 8 min or until the cheese is melted and golden</p><p>Re boil a kettle</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Wash, then chop your <strong>cavolo nero</strong> roughly, removing any tough stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped cavolo nero</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> and cook for 2-3 minutes or until wilted</p><p>Drain and add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>to the pot, then set aside until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/braised-duck-leg-with-cheesy-roast-waxy-potatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>braised duck</strong> over the sauce with the<strong> cavolo nero</strong> and <strong>cheesy waxy roast potatoes</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with a crack of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
